It is because you are passing the entire data as the body in the API request. To pass the headers separately, you need to do something as mentioned below:

    import {Headers} from &#39;angular2/http&#39;;
    var headers = new Headers();
    headers.append(key, value);
    
    // HTTP POST using these headers
    this.http.post(url, data, {
      headers: headers
    })

In your case the headers can be appended as:

    headers.append(&quot;UserId&quot;, 6);
    headers.append(&quot;created&quot;, &quot;February 4, 2016 10:13:00&quot;);

